<P>The time of this Fathers Life was long; hee
did, as <HI>Trithemius</HI> reports of him, flourish prin|cipally
<PB N="362" REF="188">
under <HI>Martian</HI> the Emperour, and dy+ed
in the yeare of Jesus Christs Incarnation
500. His body (as was fitting) was with great
solemnity and lamentation buried hard by the
body of that renouned Martyr <HI>Cassianus,</HI> and
doth with him expect a glorious resurrection
amongst the just and upright men. His Works
are of great esteeme amongst the learned,
and are to bee reserved in the
Church of Christ, as Mo|numents
of his great
labour and lear|ning.</P>
