<P>And so I will conclude this famous St. <HI>Gre|gory</HI>
his life with St. <HI>Damasce<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">s</HI> commendati|on.
<HI>Gregory</HI> was Bishop of the ancienter <HI>Roman</HI>
Church, a man admirable for his singular up|rightnesse
of life, and purity of learning, who
had as hee laboured in the sacred Mysteries of
Gods Word, an Angell to direct him, and was
inspired by the Spirit of the Holy Ghost. <HI>Da|mascenus
in Oratione de iis qui cum fide dormie|runt.</HI></P>
